text: Patissa termipunctalis is a moth in the family Crambidae. It was described by George Hampson in 1919. It is found in Malawi. The wingspan is about 16 mm. The forewings are pale pink, irrorated (sprinkled) with a few dark brown scales, as well as a slight dark brown spot ath the lower angle of the cell and a terminal series of black points. The hindwings are silvery white.Annals and Magazine of Natural History (9) 4 (23): 318 ==References== Category:Moths described in 1919 Category:Schoenobiinae
title: Patissa termipunctalis
